COMMON:

Generate your pubkey with ssh-keygen.

CLIENT:

Install the sample configuration under /etc
and change it's contents to reflect your dyndns
host.

Install the private key into /etc/dyndns.key

SERVER:

Here's example configurations for server side:

sshd_config:
Match Group dyndns
        AllowTcpForwarding no
        X11Forwarding no
        ChrootDirectory /chroots

$ ls -l /chroots/
total 6
drwxr-xr-x    2 root     wheel         512 May 27 10:40 bin
drwxr-xr-x    2 root     wheel         512 May 27 10:42 dev
drwxr-xr-x    3 root     wheel         512 May 27 11:12 home

mkdir these and copy sh into bin/

Copy MAKEDEV into dev/ and MAKEDEV std and arandom.

Copy dyndns user into home/dyndns according to passwd
file's homedirectory.

--
